**What changed:** The `aborted` boolean flag was initialized at line 94 (`aborted = False`), set at line 157 (`aborted = True`), and checked at line 195 (`if aborted: break`). Ruff F841 flagged the initial assignment as unused. I removed the flag variable entirely and replaced the outer-loop break condition with `if story_results and story_results[-1].get("status") == "aborted":` — which derives the same information from the already-recorded story result, preserving identical behavior without the flag.
